# zlx

A flexible Zipline upload client with configurable settings and command-line overrides.

## Installation

```bash
# Install to /usr/local (default)
make install

# Or install to a different location
make install PREFIX=/usr
```

## Uninstallation

```bash
make uninstall
```

## Usage

```bash
# Upload a file
zlx up file.txt

# Upload with clipboard copy
zlx up file.txt -c

# Upload with max views
zlx up file.txt -m 5

# View all commands and options
man zlx
```

## Configuration

```bash
# Set server
zlx config set servername "zipline.example.com"

# Set token
zlx config set token "your_token_here"

# View current settings
zlx config list
```

For more information, see the man page: `man zlx` 